# The `LiveRange` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

## Description {#details}

This class represents the liveness of a register, stack slot, etc.

It manages an ordered list of <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/liverange/segment">Segment</a> objects. The <a href="#ad156d10b494ea747d7c2a8776c02ca42">Segments</a> are organized in a static single assignment form: At places where a new value is defined or different values reach a CFG join a new segment with a new value number is used.

Definition at line 157 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/liveinterval-h">LiveInterval.h</a>.

### extendInBlock() {#a81f9d3d0b958e57c0c0f24982230885d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::pair&lt; VNInfo &#42;, bool &gt; LiveRange::extendInBlock (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/slotindex">SlotIndex</a> &gt; Undefs, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/slotindex">SlotIndex</a> StartIdx, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/slotindex">SlotIndex</a> Kill)</>}>
Attempt to extend a value defined after <code>StartIdx</code> to include <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a></code>.

Both <code>StartIdx</code> and <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a></code> should be in the same basic block. In case of subranges, an extension could be prevented by an explicit &quot;undef&quot; caused by a &lt;def,read-undef&gt; on a non-overlapping lane. The list of location of such &quot;undefs&quot; should be provided in <code>Undefs</code>. The return value is a pair: the first element is <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vninfo">VNInfo</a> of the value that was extended (possibly nullptr), the second is a boolean value indicating whether an &quot;undef&quot; was encountered. If this range is live before <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a></code> in the basic block that starts at <code>StartIdx</code>, and there is no intervening &quot;undef&quot;, extend it to be live up to <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a></code>, and return the pair &#123;value, false&#125;. If there is no segment before <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a></code> and there is no &quot;undef&quot; between <code>StartIdx</code> and <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a></code>, return &#123;nullptr, false&#125;. If there is an &quot;undef&quot; before <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a></code>, return &#123;nullptr, true&#125;.
